Intestinal (EII)","guid":"y7sObgMXXet4tb9mGrQOJA","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"13","text":"◊ Prevalencia estimada: 8-70%","guid":"jcTtzKHkqaT17Ic8HzVk3w","children":[]}]},{"id":"16","parent":"6","text":"› Rechazo crónico post-trasplante órgano sólido","guid":"EZLFS2mfVIbNGNtNl1Gn0g","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"6","text":"› Enfermedad Renal Crónica (ERC) con inflamación","guid":"L_VMLYpiiOeqsnMpQupFmw","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"◊ Prevalencia estimada: 23-50%","guid":"zSdaIEonJTQT1y-1d-Kr7g","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"19","parent":"1","text":"- Correlación","guid":"zoatZDuC9xhoF02WcUAsbg","children":[{"id":"20","parent":"19","text":"› Prevalencia y severidad ∝ Estadio enfermedad subyacente y Edad avanzada","guid":"VNwNJYgrM9YqFTVQa6VwhA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"21","parent":"0","text":"→ Fisiopatología (★ Impulsada inmunológicamente:\\Ncitoquinas, sistema reticuloendotelial [SRE])","guid":"zJGLGd6zCmwbGH2MJkblDg","children":[{"id":"22","parent":"21","text":"- ★ Disregulación\\NHomeostasis del Hierro (Fe)","guid":"U3BT_V0D3qZpyJpNVXYr-w","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"› Mecanismo central: ↑ Captación\\Ny retención de Fe en SRE","guid":"0aHJ-NkAdFY-cjh4tYJWxQ","children":[{"id":"24","parent":"23","text":"◊ Consecuencia: Desvío de Fe circulante → Limitación Fe disponible para eritropoyesis\\N→ ★ Eritropoyesis restringida en Fe","guid":"YmB26_ODiWsonCN7JvxbRA","children":[]}]},{"id":"25","parent":"22","text":"› Mediadores\\NMoleculares Clave:","guid":"y20kq1-X5dl1NPX_oeF4-A","children":[{"id":"26","parent":"25","text":"◊ ★ Citoquinas\\Nproinflamatorias:","guid":"t_EifYSs8ICrAY_f-ur-BQ","children":[{"id":"27","parent":"26","text":"• TNF-α: Induce hipoferremia, ↑ ferritina, estimula eritrofagocitosis, inhibe producción EPO, inhibe progenitores eritroides, inhibe Hepcidina. ⇄ Homeostasis Fe, Eritropoyesis","guid":"tF4ycY_xag_q49VSnbMC5A","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"26","text":"• IL-1: Induce hipoferremia, ↑ ferritina, inhibe producción EPO, inhibe progenitores eritroides. ⇄ Homeostasis Fe, Eritropoyesis","guid":"Ax4xFFQybaHaoshR0XIBhg","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"26","text":"• IL-6: ★ Induce expresión hepática de Hepcidina, ↑ ferritina. ⇄ Homeostasis Fe (vía Hepcidina)","guid":"HjrZctO-bGJbbiF9PXLxmQ","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"26","text":"• IFN-γ: ↑ Expresión DMT1 (↑ captación Fe macrófagos), ↓ Expresión Ferroportina 1 (↓ salida Fe macrófagos),\\N★ Potente inhibidor progenitores eritroides. ⇄ Homeostasis Fe, Eritropoyesis","guid":"IgrMZPrxDB_8PZ2uWdM6Bg","children":[]}]},{"id":"31","parent":"25","text":"◊ Lipopolisacárido (LPS): Similar a IFN-γ en transportadores Fe, Induce Hepcidina. ⇄ Homeostasis Fe","guid":"4pemqBHh9BKI3byEwDW4Jw","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"25","text":"◊ Citoquina antiinflamatoria:","guid":"JgcIREgjhyd07LlLQGUPSA","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"• IL-10: ↑ Expresión Receptor Transferrina (↑ captación Fe), ↑ traducción Ferritina (↑ almacenamiento Fe). ⇄ Homeostasis Fe","guid":"8Xa8B7GFTAXUUWRGrwbH4g","children":[]}]},{"id":"34","parent":"25","text":"◊ ★ ★ Hepcidina:","guid":"dEb_PWCTrJ6_UrJVsZ7SYQ","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"• Naturaleza: Péptido (25 aa), proteína fase aguda, regulador hormonal del Fe.","guid":"i2riEQtKRXuoFdljJ6XuLQ","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"34","text":"• Regulación: Inducida por IL-6, LPS; Inhibida por TNF-α.","guid":"wi9hIiaStwlOjFCJ8mv-KA","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"34","text":"• Función: ↓ Absorción duodenal Fe; ↓ Liberación Fe macrófagos (bloquea Ferroportina 1). ★ Central en hipoferremia inflamatoria.","guid":"NyTNI1XHx8CVde4OMljhbA","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"34","text":"• Evidencia experimental: Sobreexpresión → Anemia ferropénica severa (ratones);\\NDeficiencia → Previene hipoferremia inflamatoria (ratones).","guid":"1FdEP9WKY2y-0RYmfdcbfg","children":[]}]},{"id":"39","parent":"25","text":"◊ Hemojuvelina (HFE2): Posible co-regulador con hepcidina.","guid":"9ReLCUGBT3gmo4H0QL7EzQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"40","parent":"22","text":"› Otros mecanismos:","guid":"zkpLEJq4SsTrO0UZBXzJDQ","children":[{"id":"41","parent":"40","text":"◊ ↑ Eritrofagocitosis: Inducida por TNF-α, daño membrana GR.","guid":"bgx0beZHsuCSJRJlFPIlUA","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"40","text":"◊ ↑ Expresión Ferritina: Almacenamiento Fe en SRE.","guid":"utFMKpGvl3IdgGvWmBAfNQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"43","parent":"21","text":"- Deterioro Proliferación\\NProgenitores Eritroides\\N(BFU-E, CFU-E)","guid":"IEhNw_3PVpe2QJxoJLD7GQ","children":[{"id":"44","parent":"43","text":"› ★ Inhibición directa por Citoquinas: IFN-γ (más potente), TNF-α, IL-1, IFN-α/β.","guid":"oUsYmOAg6om6F7ReBVP1Wg","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"43","text":"› Mecanismos\\Nsubyacentes:","guid":"3XVIb17Hngcc3I7VCJYJ1Q","children":[{"id":"46","parent":"45","text":"◊ Inducción apoptosis (¿vía ceramida?).","guid":"44ijZkqUR9FMQzIx6YyrLw","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"45","text":"◊ ↓ Expresión receptores EPO en progenitores.","guid":"Oxtw6Thyti8bF6bGGcVMgw","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"45","text":"◊ Toxicidad directa por radicales libres (NO, O2-) inducidos por citoquinas en macrófagos vecinos.","guid":"Hdv3nvkwra2rjSovkuJPbA","children":[]}]},{"id":"49","parent":"43","text":"› Factores\\Ncontribuyentes:","guid":"mJzegwXYynEfqLqk7coGpA","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"◊ Limitación disponibilidad Fe (resultado de disregulación).","guid":"QNrXeFOZIuXDJaWdYEuWTw","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"49","text":"◊ Infiltración médula ósea (tumor, microorganismos - VIH, VHC, malaria).","guid":"lPSbgzEuCX0Gw90aWOpmmg","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"49","text":"◊ Producción local de citoquinas/radicales por células tumorales.","guid":"2cnOmIkjquLvEvZUuJuIGA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"53","parent":"21","text":"- Respuesta Disminuida de\\NEritropoyetina (EPO)","guid":"N8IGeavA79CrAKZK24lhjw","children":[{"id":"54","parent":"53","text":"› Niveles EPO séricos: Inadecuadamente bajos para el grado de anemia (mayoría de casos).","guid":"56gccsPsZK1t_LtqdVINag","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"53","text":"› Inhibición Producción EPO (renal): Mediada por IL-1, TNF-α; posible rol de radicales libres.","guid":"LpEOQQRz7kxJeWEAYtFwlw","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"53","text":"› ↓ Sensibilidad\\NProgenitores a EPO:","guid":"qEJZK5jM9CRsgJtDW5M03w","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"◊ Relacionado con ↑ niveles IFN-γ, TNF-α.","guid":"x7RxXTRjKxS6EL4wyBylfg","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"◊ Afectación vías señalización intracelular post-receptor EPO.","guid":"ZtTNGCgE6Obo4TbYWw9RBA","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"56","text":"◊ ↓ Expresión receptores EPO (inducida por citoquinas).","guid":"DYyIUhLNUANeMnuDw6Xv3g","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"56","text":"◊ Limitación disponibilidad Fe.","guid":"5_yHLjrtF2k5k8yQf26d1Q","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"21","text":"- Reducción Vida\\NMedia Eritrocitos","guid":"A5kNwTR-XlMTm_dPgPg8Qg","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"› ↑ Eritrofagocitosis.","guid":"yP42zB0WsgOJnN7PPNzZrg","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"61","text":"› Daño directo a eritrocitos por citoquinas/radicales libres.","guid":"0VeAHLzk_Aunluc5CiSt0w","children":[]}]},{"id":"64","parent":"21","text":"- Otros Factores\\NAgravantes","guid":"JY8rGZ5Dhxw4nhSIJ5pdig","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"› Sangrado coexistente.","guid":"9NKvqyKgW1i5G9MFottAhw","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"64","text":"› Deficiencias vitamínicas (B12, Ácido Fólico).","guid":"mgtCBDK20uk7LrTKqJTHyw","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"64","text":"› Hiperesplenismo.","guid":"-Pla3VxHogAo3zYNLv_5rA","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"64","text":"› Hemólisis autoinmune.","guid":"7oAljk06jH13tyuktRV7_A","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"64","text":"› Disfunción renal asociada (↓EPO, toxinas urémicas).","guid":"SoSa1QtV9ZqgjNBW5_dqDQ","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"64","text":"› Radio/Quimioterapia.","guid":"9OUaWuD2GVJTHyzW99g_xQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"71","parent":"0","text":"→ Evaluación\\NDiagnóstica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"72","parent":"71","text":"- Hallazgos Hematológicos\\NGenerales","guid":"kCD3gfXhTaFEvPH8TgQGYg","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"› Anemia: Típicamente normocítica, normocrómica.","guid":"3lrwDHqWqBF3P4IyeB4-KQ","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"72","text":"› Severidad: Leve (Hb ~9.5 g/dL) a Moderada (Hb ~8 g/dL).","guid":"5LUnuyoUpk2HtF01VFeVKQ","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"72","text":"› Reticulocitos: Bajos (indica hipoproducción).","guid":"GqLzC-VvyEhLP0N7fgEeFA","children":[]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"71","text":"- ★ Estudio del Metabolismo del Hierro (★ Diferenciación\\Nclave de Anemia Ferropénica [AF]) (Ver Algoritmo Fig. 2)","guid":"IJDPMyZf6dHg7Qj9yxJ06g","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"› Hierro Sérico: ↓ (en ambas).","guid":"VS1JTFh-fL_XW0YXZ1EdLg","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"76","text":"› Saturación de Transferrina (SatTf): ↓ (en ambas, usualmente <16%).","guid":"f3yk638N3AiK2Y9ldyp5Og","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"76","text":"› Transferrina Sérica (TIBC): Normal o ↓ (en ACD); ↑ (en AF).","guid":"-zt-cn0plJH-e5d8lrf-1g","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"76","text":"› ★ ★ Ferritina\\NSérica:","guid":"N9mKB8m9Hl2gLoK3dJr7-Q","children":[{"id":"81","parent":"80","text":"◊ ACD pura: Normal o ↑ (refleja ↑ depósitos SRE + reactante fase aguda). (>100 ng/mL)","guid":"pLWCl653EvK6RdPJ90Th-Q","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"80","text":"◊ AF pura: ↓ (<15-30 ng/mL indica depósitos bajos/ausentes).","guid":"j1Kx_n_lVNvdHzsM8yCx6g","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"80","text":"◊ ACD + AF coexistente: ↓ o normal-bajo (30-100 ng/mL).","guid":"W52OirkJEw8GVyxOJJSBeA","children":[]}]},{"id":"84","parent":"76","text":"› ★ Receptor Soluble de\\NTransferrina (sTfR):","guid":"0a9lCDIGg-YrmO7IUwHDiA","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"◊ ACD pura: Normal (expresión afectada por citoquinas).","guid":"s9nboN299IGsFxXOdTES4Q","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"84","text":"◊ AF (pura o coexistente): ↑.","guid":"xlgAmmtF7z9zh13_WJLgHQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"87","parent":"76","text":"› ★ ★ Ratio sTfR /\\Nlog Ferritina:","guid":"eVAt9x2iNhr-E35urSK4Gg","children":[{"id":"88","parent":"87","text":"◊ < 1 : Sugiere ACD pura.","guid":"ESk_2S8kmnTJdh0DBA6QEw","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"87","text":"◊ > 2 : Sugiere AF (absoluta) coexistente con ACD.","guid":"cBwuCPJhstLrp2Q7etIzrQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"90","parent":"76","text":"› % Eritrocitos Hipocrómicos / Contenido Hb Reticulocitaria (CHr):\\NÚtil para detectar eritropoyesis restringida en Fe funcional.","guid":"eNKl9BUCua7KH93Gjpm2NQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"91","parent":"71","text":"- Niveles de\\NEritropoyetina (EPO)","guid":"tXbsQsl3_pW8dea_sCu1Bw","children":[{"id":"92","parent":"91","text":"› Utilidad: Principalmente si Hb < 10 g/dL.","guid":"fZ16T9EQUiPrjFgP9yw4Pw","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"91","text":"› Interpretación: Considerar grado de anemia.","guid":"2XYgDpfxuywEmeRlt4y7fw","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"91","text":"› Valor predictivo (respuesta a\\NAgentes Eritropoyéticos [AE]):","guid":"DFNQXvLBpTQLOywpy637eQ","children":[{"id":"95","parent":"94","text":"◊ EPO >100 U/L o Ferritina >400 ng/mL → Predice MALA respuesta (en Cáncer sin QT).","guid":"kE7gRyk80RBXitI2iNhbtg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"96","parent":"71","text":"- Otros","guid":"PaRZ2oDk9dx09U23YcxHHw","children":[{"id":"97","parent":"96","text":"› Citoquinas séricas: ↑ (en ACD).","guid":"X27QjMXORUMHmJ8mcvDf5w","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"96","text":"› Descartar otras causas de anemia.","guid":"jpH5HsKXmQa_FSr4EjsrnQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"99","parent":"0","text":"→ Tratamiento","guid":"nEnmBSJOyh2piOvbcNAXjQ","children":[{"id":"100","parent":"99","text":"- Racionalidad\\Ny Objetivos","guid":"4e0ZBqKVL3vaHOL5nhawTg","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"› Impacto negativo de la anemia: ↑ Gasto cardíaco, Asociación peor pronóstico (Cáncer, ERC, ICC),\\N↓ Calidad de Vida.","guid":"KwxCwCog9lPjIOBD55jadg","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"100","text":"› ★ Objetivo Hb: 11-12 g/dL (Recomendado por guías).","guid":"b4n4tRGSW5OWAemLFHUrpg","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"100","text":"› ★ Precaución: Normalización Hb (>12 g/dL o Hct >42%) puede ser perjudicial\\N(↑ mortalidad en ERC, estudio Besarab et al. 1998).","guid":"D4RSVgU3s_A-5Fm8woeVzQ","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"100","text":"› Frecuente subdiagnóstico y subtratamiento.","guid":"veDaX3UaoDvXATIcBhNqiQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"99","text":"- Opciones Terapéuticas\\N(Tabla 4)","guid":"E3YXkqn-oFMIIwzIBUKuvw","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"› ★ ★ Tratamiento Enfermedad Subyacente: ★ Terapia de elección si es posible.","guid":"1QaV9ylY3NLkkzxHV40Gfw","children":[{"id":"107","parent":"106","text":"◊ Ejemplo: Anti-TNF en AR mejora Hb.","guid":"617yq5SMgdA2FtAybSBBpw","children":[]}]},{"id":"108","parent":"105","text":"› Transfusiones\\Nde Sangre","guid":"_W3xQGnSueQGF2ggLpJaPg","children":[{"id":"109","parent":"108","text":"◊ Indicaciones: Corrección rápida, anemia severa (Hb <8 g/dL) o amenazante (Hb <6.5 g/dL), sangrado agudo.","guid":"0_1iz0rW4SurL9alQXmehQ","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"108","text":"◊ Limitaciones: No recomendada a largo plazo (riesgo sobrecarga Fe, aloinmunización HLA);\\Nseguridad controvertida (inmunomodulación?, resultados variables en UCI vs IAM).","guid":"9EQQP42iTld_xD531fB7dw","children":[]}]},{"id":"111","parent":"105","text":"› ★ Terapia con Hierro","guid":"Sw5MbiR18wnqFoCW2KS4_w","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"◊ Oral: Absorción limitada por Hepcidina; Fe absorbido desviado a SRE.","guid":"YV_9CzHhZ_bublsy9Wa3xA","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"111","text":"◊ ★ Parenteral (IV):","guid":"-lzjehzZytmfQ2neF3HM8g","children":[{"id":"114","parent":"113","text":"• Indicaciones:","guid":"faTNpr_zK7I0YbtE5jn73g","children":[{"id":"115","parent":"114","text":"◊ ★ Déficit absoluto de Fe coexistente (tratamiento necesario).","guid":"5xg4Pld-x_LcQ18_Nuwtuw","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"114","text":"◊ ★ ★ Déficit funcional de Hierro (DFH): Considerar si hay pobre respuesta a AE. Mejora respuesta a AE.","guid":"5eOgQKrRKj8_KJoCQplGrA","children":[]}]},{"id":"117","parent":"113","text":"• ★ Controversias /\\NRiesgos Potenciales:","guid":"Zx_TgJgi8z3dS6wTZ1T7XA","children":[{"id":"118","parent":"117","text":"◊ Nutriente para microbios/tumores?.","guid":"ZQGzemaeiRSAYVHsEuwMKA","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"117","text":"◊ ↑ Riesgo bacteriemia en hemodiálisis (con SatTf>20%, Ferritina>100).","guid":"1H5FKtcLKLQZ08vptn9-gw","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"117","text":"◊ Estrés oxidativo (radicales hidroxilo), riesgo CV.","guid":"VwgiW4rAr0BwWM_8Z0C1_A","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"117","text":"◊ Efecto inmunosupresor? (↓ vías IFN-γ).","guid":"Tej1W9bf5KUG2StJwBQD-g","children":[]}]},{"id":"122","parent":"113","text":"• ★ Precaución: Generalmente NO recomendado si Ferritina normal/alta (>100 ng/mL)\\Nen ausencia de DFH demostrado o déficit absoluto.","guid":"nnESZZLAWipOadltDJiykQ","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"113","text":"• Beneficios potenciales: ↓ TNF-α? (AR, ERC). Buena respuesta en EII.","guid":"UUuZuYNMcu6588OkCoprOQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"124","parent":"105","text":"› ★ Agentes Eritropoyéticos\\N(AE)","guid":"vN9PQpot0gws31EYUJ36LQ","children":[{"id":"125","parent":"124","text":"◊ Tipos: Epoetina alfa, Epoetina beta, Darbepoetina alfa.","guid":"gHN88T2fJFVmycZKitBfMA","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"124","text":"◊ Aprobaciones: Cáncer (con QT), ERC, VIH (con tto. mielosupresor).","guid":"yI4dM3Mcw3tyRocAoipMlQ","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"124","text":"◊ Mecanismo: Supera inhibición citoquinas, estimula eritropoyesis.","guid":"7RO74Sqt7I2wbY_02V66Lw","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"124","text":"◊ Eficacia variable: Respuesta 25% (SMD) a 95% (AR, ERC).","guid":"xztSWu0G5Gf3Ro2VewHi-g","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"124","text":"◊ Pobre respuesta: Asociada a ↑ citoquinas proinflamatorias, ↓ disponibilidad Fe.","guid":"AhrzyW0g_qNDeFxZ1Lie7w","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"124","text":"◊ ★ ★ Riesgos / Efectos\\NAdversos Potenciales:","guid":"_bXiJvrJPH3Sn4cRl7M_Ng","children":[{"id":"131","parent":"130","text":"• ★ Aplasia Pura Serie Roja (APSR): Rara, asociada a formulación Eprex sin albúmina (1998-2004), incidencia ↓ con manejo adecuado.","guid":"pB-_ookWfktByEIQQ6dx0w","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"130","text":"• ★ Receptores EPO en Células Tumorales: Expresión en varios cánceres (mama, ovario, etc.). Rol en progresión tumoral controvertido.\\NPosible inducción neoangiogénesis.","guid":"uHuU5crVNYj7CzqmcXGHSg","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"130","text":"• ★ ★ Riesgo asociado a sobrecorrección Hb (>12 g/dL).","guid":"EOzOrfpVJao0AtpeZysmFQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"134","parent":"124","text":"◊ Monitorización\\NTerapia AE:","guid":"pGrr3Izm5faR76b7i-WYDg","children":[{"id":"135","parent":"134","text":"• Evaluar estado Fe antes de iniciar y durante tto (buscar DFH).","guid":"xKIq-n_cuXCv7vQvyYXe3g","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"134","text":"• Control Hb: 4 semanas inicial, luego c/2-4 sem.","guid":"4liTx90zyHUrTKk2qklSSw","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"134","text":"• Ajuste dosis: Si ↑ Hb < 1 g/dL en 4 sem (y Fe OK), escalar dosis 50%. Ajustar para mantener Hb 11-12 g/dL.","guid":"G-9EKe1-0jvEI2zvizXmNg","children":[]},{"id":"138","parent":"134","text":"• No respondedor: Sin respuesta en 8 sem con dosis óptima y sin déficit Fe.","guid":"Tg0nyuQ9bjCEqyCFmQDeQg","children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"id":"139","parent":"0","text":"→ Conclusiones y\\NDirecciones Futuras","guid":"","children":[{"id":"140","parent":"139","text":"- Necesidad de Estudios\\NProspectivos Controlados","guid":"nWR8sUbRdbf0gdp7Jes7iA","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"› Evaluar impacto real del manejo de anemia sobre enfermedad subyacente.","guid":"dSrl1xfHrdOkLbU6uRfccA","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"140","text":"› Clarificar significado clínico de receptores EPO tumorales.","guid":"rC2706aDyfHG_iVhGOjgYQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"143","parent":"139","text":"- Estrategias Terapéuticas\\NFuturas Potenciales","guid":"lRomJOFUJ1_7WOmrK0tj0Q","children":[{"id":"144","parent":"143","text":"› Quelantes de hierro (para inducir EPO endógena?).","guid":"J-j3yFdo9RbohbL5XyMVCg","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"143","text":"› ★ Antagonistas de Hepcidina.","guid":"QXGBLvKP0HSw2INshVgsNw","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"143","text":"› Moduladores de citoquinas / Nuevos estimulantes eritropoyesis.","guid":"ARK6dlYQck9I1kDeSAS0sQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"147","parent":"139","text":"- Objetivo Final","guid":"9UfEloFJzu0eZ40VuS2kgw","children":[{"id":"148","parent":"147","text":"› Identificar régimen terapéutico óptimo basado en mejoría de morbilidad y mortalidad.","guid":"jbpdooJZi1tfeeJVcxroBw","children":[]}]}]}]},"node_count":148,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Hematología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Hematología","filename":"Paper. Anemia de enfermedad crónica-2025-1","id":"map_1063","resolved_references":[]}